{{Sangam literature}}
'''Nagan Devanar,''' known in full as Madurai Tamil Koothan Nagan Devanar ([[Tamil language|Tamil]]: மதுரைத் தமிழ்க் கூத்தன் நாகன்தேவனார்), was a poet of the [[Sangam period]], to whom a sole verse of the Sangam literature has been attributed, in addition to verse 12 of the [[Tiruvalluva Maalai]].<ref name="Vedanayagam_Urai">{{cite book | last = Vedanayagam | first = Rama | author-link = | title = திருவள்ளுவ மாலை மூலமும் எளிய உரை விளக்கமும் [Tiruvalluva Maalai: Moolamum Eliya Urai Vilakkamum] | publisher = Manimekalai Prasuram | series = | volume = | edition = 1 | date = 2017 | location = Chennai | pages = 24–25 | language = Tamil | url = | doi = | id = | isbn = | mr = | zbl = | jfm = }}</ref>
==Biography== Nagan Devanar was born as "Devanar" and lived in [[Madurai]]. He was known for his expertise in the ancient Tamil theatre.<ref name="SangaIlakkiyam_3">{{cite book | last = Kowmareeshwari (Ed.) | first = S. | author-link = | title = அகநானூறு, புறநானூறு [Agananuru, Purananuru] | publisher = Saradha Pathippagam | series = Sanga Ilakkiyam | volume = 3 | edition = 1 | date = August 2012 | location = Chennai | pages = 403 (Book II) | language = Tamil | url = | doi = | id = | isbn = | mr = | zbl = | jfm = }}</ref>
==Contribution to the Sangam literature== Nagan Devanar has written a sole Sangam verse—verse 164 of the [[Agananuru]]—apart from verse 12 of the [[Tiruvalluva Maalai]].<ref name="SangaIlakkiyam_3"/>
