{{notability|biography|date=October 2018}} {{Infobox Hindu leader | name = Panth Maharaj | image = Colorized_Photograph_of_Panth_Maharaj.jpg | caption = Photograph of Panth Maharaj | alt = Panth Maharaj | birth_date = {{Birth date|def=yes|1855|03|03}} | birth_name = Dattatreya Panth | nationality = [[Indian people|Indian]] | guru = [[Balmukund]] | philosophy = [[Avadhooth]], [[Hinduism]] | literary_works = ''[[Shri Datta Prem Lahari]]'' }}
'''Panth Maharaj''' (3 March 1855 – 1905), born '''Dattopant Balekundrikar''', was a [[Hindu]] spiritual master who is regarded by his devotees as a saint and lived in the [[Belgavi]] region of [[India]].
==Background== Panth Maharaj was born in a [[Deshastha Brahmin]] family to Ramachandra Panth and Sitabai on the March 9th, 1855 in [[Belgaum]] which coincided with the auspicious Hindu holiday of [[Krishna Janmashtami]].<ref name="aboutbelgaum">{{ cite web |url=https://allaboutbelgaum.com/lifestyle/panchamukhi-sadguru-shri-pant-maharaj-balekundrikar/ |title=Panchamukhi Sadguru Shri Pant Maharaj Balekundrikar |date=2018-10-27 |accessdate=2018-11-16 |website=All About Belgaum}}</ref> He is considered to be great Hindu saint who founded a philosophy in which Nav Narayan of Avadhoot Sampradaya are attributed to Dattatreya.<ref>http://pantmaharaj.com/Biography.html</ref>
==Legacy== The main temple dedicated to Panth Maharaj is located in the village of [[Balekundri_(B.K.)|Balekundari]] on the outskirts of [[Belgavi]]. The temple houses the wooden shoes, or [[paduka]]s, worn by him. Behind the temple is an [[Ficus_racemosa|Indian fig tree]] marking the spot where he was cremated and an eternal flame that has been kept burning from his funeral pyre.<ref name="aboutbelgaum"></ref>
